<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFFCFFC3FF71FCCDFC69FC43" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFCFFC3FF71FCCDFDD6FC97" blockId="20.[151,1436,762,1005]" box="[151,555,799,825]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFFCFFC3FF79FCCDFF05FC97" box="[159,248,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="67.[151,250,1945,1969]" captionTargetBox="[193,1394,196,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-19@67.[184,1403,181,1922]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="FIGURE 14. Southeast Asian Eudocima and Eudocima tyrannus group adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605535" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605535/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Figs 14</figureCitation>
: I–J, 21: F, 26: Q–T, 32:H)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFCFFC3FF71FC91FC69FC43" blockId="20.[151,1436,762,1005]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
This small species (
<quantity id="A21252CFFFFCFFC3FE9FFC90FE05FCF3" box="[377,504,834,861]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.45" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="3.4" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="34.5" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="34.0">34–35 mm</quantity>
, n=6) is similar in size to another island endemic, 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFCFFC3FBA6FC91FB5FFCF3" baseAuthorityName="Robinson" baseAuthorityYear="1968" box="[1088,1186,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paulii">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFCFFC3FBA6FC91FB5FFCF3" box="[1088,1186,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">E. paulii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but in 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFCFFC3FB1BFC91FA8CFCF2" authorityName="Zilli &amp; Brou" authorityYear="2017" box="[1277,1393,835,860]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martini">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFCFFC3FB1BFC91FA8CFCF2" box="[1277,1393,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">E. martini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the hindwings have no medial patch. Members of the 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFCFFC3FD22FCB5FCB1FC2F" baseAuthorityName="Hubner" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[708,844,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="homaena">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFCFFC3FD22FCB5FCB1FC2F" box="[708,844,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C. homaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group also have no medial patch but lack a green dot inside the reniform, and the females have a green transverse bar across the forewing. This species also has unique genitalia including a thin aedeagus and uncus and small juxta (
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFFCFFC3FCBAFC7DFBEEFC67" author="Zilli, A. &amp; Brou, V. A. &amp; Klem, C. &amp; Zaspel, J." box="[860,1043,943,969]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="152 - 166" refId="ref41849" refString="Zilli, A., Brou, V. A., Klem, C. &amp; Zaspel, J. (2017) The Eudocima Billberg, 1820 of the Australian Region (Lepidoptera: Erebidae). In: Telnov, D. (Ed.), Biodiversity, Biogeography and Nature Conservation in Wallacea and New Guinea. Vol. 3. The Entomological Society of Latvia, Riga, pp. 631 - 655, pls. 152 - 166." type="book chapter" year="2017">
Zilli 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFCFFC3FC70FC7DFC3AFC67" box="[918,967,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). This species is rare in collections and is apparently endemic to the 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFCFFC3FDEFFC01FD39FC43" box="[521,708,979,1005]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFFCFFC3FD32FC01FC75FC43" author="Zilli, A. &amp; Brou, V. A. &amp; Klem, C. &amp; Zaspel, J." box="[724,904,979,1005]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="152 - 166" refId="ref41849" refString="Zilli, A., Brou, V. A., Klem, C. &amp; Zaspel, J. (2017) The Eudocima Billberg, 1820 of the Australian Region (Lepidoptera: Erebidae). In: Telnov, D. (Ed.), Biodiversity, Biogeography and Nature Conservation in Wallacea and New Guinea. Vol. 3. The Entomological Society of Latvia, Riga, pp. 631 - 655, pls. 152 - 166." type="book chapter" year="2017">
Zilli 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFCFFC3FCEAFC01FCC0FC43" box="[780,829,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
